om/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ulordcindrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Cindrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Councellor</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/16/01 11:39:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanes &amp; RVR</span><hr size=1> I play Glamis (obviously), a level 44 Thane. In my experience, shield and parry are damn near useless in RvR. You almost never get blocks or parries in melee against players, and shields are nowhere near good enough against archers.<br><br>The only good use I have found for my shield in RvR is when I get attacked by a ranger in a keep attack, I /face it and use engage. This generally keeps the ranger busy and unable to kill anyone.<br><br>Stormcalling rocks for RvR. You should definitely train stormcalling anytime you get a chance to raise mjollnir, toothgnasher, or thunder AE. These 3 spells are great in RvR. IMHO, thors lightning is not very useful in RvR (though its good in PvE).<br><br>I have a 20 in shield and 12 in parry. This does help me in PvE which obviously is important for levelling up and gaining magic items. Unless something changes, I am not planning on training them much higher.<br><br>My general philosophy for thanes is to train hammer or stormcalling based on whatever style or spell is close. If a really good style is close, I go for it. If a really good spell is close, I switch focus to stormcalling. It seems to work. <p>-Glamis Askamelodi, Thane of Thor<BR>http://www.threshold-rpg.com</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ronod>Ronod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/17/01 2:16:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanes &amp; RVR</span><hr size=1> This be very valuable information - would you mind re-posting it in the new &quot;Basic Strategy for RvR&quot; thread? - Might even consider adding any additional info that might be helpful to other Thanes. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/unaraa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>naraa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/17/01 2:35:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanes &amp; RVR</span><hr size=1> Thank you Glamis, I appreciate the counsel. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/btheclanmaclear.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=agravainebyremore>Agravaine Byremore</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>High Councellor</span><br>  Posts: 539<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/20/01 7:12:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanes &amp; RVR</span><hr size=1> I have currently 15 in hammer, 23 in stormcalling, 11 in swords, 12 in shields, and 10 in parry.  I find that against archers, a shield is actually a very good thing to have.  I have only been shot by archers a few times, but with my shield skill and my magical shield, I find that I block about every fifth arrow.  I also find that when fighting monsters, I block at an incredible rate, upwards of 1/4 of their attacks.<br><br>The way I have learned to use guard and protect is this: put protect on the main healer (or other caster) and guard on the main tank.  You are alost never close enough to the healer to guard them effectively, but thanes are often right next to the main tank.  Guard allows you to block an attack against another player, so if you can block an attack against the main tank, you save the healer power and agro.<br><br>I will also admit that I have next to no experience in RvR at all, so take my advice with a grain of salt.<br><br>Duelin <p><img src="http://members.home.net/geist22/sigs/Agravaine.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4F4F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/unaraa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>naraa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(12/22/01 3:06:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=173.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanes &amp; RVR</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info and suggestions Duelin..   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/uonahoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Onahoo</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble</span><br> 